Receipt Upload v1 — Manual Testing Checklist
1. Access & Permissions

 Regular member sees "➕ Quick Expense" in the sidebar after signing in

 Unassigned / signed-out user does NOT see the sidebar button

 Quick Expense page opens as a full-width overlay (Back to Dashboard returns correctly)

 Quick Entry and Scan Receipt tabs are both visible on the overlay
2. Upload & OCR (Scan Receipt tab)

 File picker accepts .jpg, .jpeg, .png, .webp, .pdf; rejects other types

 Uploading a clear grocery receipt image → OCR extracts merchant, date, and line items with amounts pre-filled

 Uploading a blurry/unreadable image → app shows "OCR could not extract line items. Add lines manually." and opens an empty review screen (does not crash)

 Uploading when [openai] api_key is blank in secrets → same graceful fallback to manual entry (no error thrown)

 Receipt date override field is respected (change date before uploading → review screen shows that date)
3. Draft List

 After uploading, navigating away and back to Scan Receipt → the draft appears in the "Resume a draft receipt" list

 Clicking Resume on a draft loads the review screen with previously saved lines

 Clicking 🗑 archives the draft; it disappears from the list immediately
4. Review Screen — Header

 Merchant, Date, and Total fields are editable and pre-filled from OCR

 Changing merchant/date/total and clicking Save Draft → values persist when resuming the draft

 If a storage image was uploaded, an expandable Receipt image section shows the preview
5. Review Screen — Line Editor

 Each line shows Description, Amount, and Ledger Target

 Regular member: Ledger target dropdown only shows Personal (and HH Obligation if they have obligation assignments)

 Admin/developer: Ledger target shows all four options (Personal, HH Obligation, HH Shared, Project)

 Switching ledger target updates the Category picker to match that target's options

 Switching to Project hides the Category picker and shows the Project selector instead

 ＋ Add line button appends a blank row

 Entering a non-numeric amount → field is ignored at post time (soft, not a hard block in v1)
6. Category Picker & Inline Create

 Personal line → shows only that member's personal categories

 HH Obligation line → shows only that member's assigned obligation categories

 HH Shared line → shows household shared categories (admin only)

 Project line → shows active project list only

 "Add new category" expander for personal target → entering parent + sub + budget and clicking Create → new category appears in the picker on next reload of the review screen

 "Add new category" for hh_shared → non-admin sees "Only admins can create Household categories" message, no form

 "Add new category" for project → shows "Projects are managed in the Projects module" message, no form
7. Save Draft

 Clicking Save Draft without posting → "Draft saved." confirmation; no expense rows appear in Budget → Expenses

 Resuming the draft afterward shows the same lines in the same state
8. Post to Ledger — Happy Paths

 Personal line with category → expense appears in that member's Personal ledger under the selected category

 HH Obligation line with category → expense appears in the Household ledger under the obligation category; member's personal ledger reflects it if integration is on

 HH Shared line with category (admin) → expense appears in the Household shared budget

 Project line with project selected → project actual cost increments; expense logged under the Projects category

 All lines posted successfully → receipt status changes to posted; review screen closes and returns to the upload form
9. Post to Ledger — Uncategorized Fallback

 Allow uncategorized ON (default): posting a personal line with no category selected → Receipt / Uncategorized personal category is auto-created and the expense lands there

 Allow uncategorized ON: posting an HH Shared line with no category → Receipt / Uncategorized HH category created; expense lands there

 Allow uncategorized OFF: posting any line with no category → error message "Category required. Select a category or enable uncategorized posting."

 HH Obligation line with no category → always blocked regardless of the uncategorized toggle (no safe default bucket)

 Project line with no project selected → always blocked with "No project selected for this line."

 Expenses in Receipt / Uncategorized are visible and editable in Budget → Expenses (one-time expenses list) for later recategorization
10. Partial Post & Error Recovery

 Mix of valid and invalid lines (e.g., one personal line ready, one obligation line without a category) → valid line posts; failed line shows inline error; review screen stays open with failed lines editable

 After fixing a failed line, clicking Post again → remaining line posts; receipt marked posted
11. Permission Guardrails (server-side)

 Regular member cannot select hh_shared or project ledger target (UI hides them; even if tampered, DB write returns false)

 Member posting to an obligation category not in their assignment list → log_household_expense_from_personal rejects it; error shown

 Receipt draft not visible to another household member who didn't upload it (and is not admin)
12. Edge Cases

 Uploading a second receipt while a draft is already open → draft list shows both; each resumes independently

 Receipt with a single line item → posts normally (no "empty lines" error)

 Line amount of $0.00 or blank → blocked with "Amount must be greater than zero" at post time

 Very long description (200+ chars) → truncated gracefully; does not break the layout